Addax Petroleum, the Nigerian unit of
 China Petroleum & Chemical Corp. (600028) , or Sinopec, plans to boost oil
output to more than 85,000 barrels a day by the end of 2012.  Addax currently produces 75,000 barrels daily from over 90
wells at its onshore Oil Mining Lease 124 and offshore OML 123
and 126, the company said in a statement on its  website .  Sinopec bought Addax in 2009, adding reserves in Nigeria,
Cameroon and Gabon.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
